# Auto-push to GitHub

After completing any code change task in this repo:

1. Verify the build passes when the change affects app code (`npm run build`).
2. Commit all relevant changes with a concise message focused on why.
3. Push to `origin main` immediately — do not ask the user for confirmation first.
4. Mention the commit hash and that GitHub Actions will redeploy to https://buildpilotapp.github.io/CampReady/

Skip commit/push only when:
- The user explicitly says not to push.
- There are no file changes to commit.
- The task is question-only or review-only with no code edits.

Do not push secrets (`.env`, credentials, etc.).
